bject\\n- noticeType: Type of notice (Maintenance, Capacity Constraint, Force Majeure, etc.)\\n- status: Initiate, Supersede, or Cancel\\n- postedDate: When notice was posted (ISO 8601)\\n- effectiveDate: When notice takes effect (ISO 8601)\\n- endDate: When notice expires (ISO 8601, null if none)\\n- description: Main content/body of the notice (cleaned text, not HTML)\\n- affectedLocations: List of affected locations/meters if mentioned\\n- responseRequired: true if response is required, false otherwise\\n\\nReturn ONLY valid JSON, no markdown or explanation.\\n\\nHTML Content:\\n<!-- template.asp -->\\r\\n<html><head><title>Algonquin Gas Transmission, LLC 006951446 : Critical Notices</title><link rel=stylesheet href='/styles/infopost.css' type='text/css'><link rel=stylesheet href='NoticeDetail.css' type='text/css'></head><body><div id=main><script type='text/javascript'> function Print() {if (document.queryCommandSupported('print')) {document.execCommand('print', false, null);\\t}else {window.parent.print(); }}</script><div class=recordsetBar><a class=recordsetBar href='javascript:history.go(-1)'>Back</a><a class=recordsetBar href='#' onClick='Print();return false'>Print</a></div><div id=bulletinContents><div class=headingArea><div id=heading>TSP:&nbsp<br>TSP Name:&nbsp<br>Critical Notice Description:&nbsp<br>Notice Effective Date:&nbsp<br>Notice Effective Time:&nbsp<br>Notice End Date:&nbsp<br>Notice End Time:&nbsp<br>Notice Identifier:&nbsp<br>Notice Status Description:&nbsp<br>Notice Type:&nbsp<br>Posting Date:&nbsp<br>Posting Time:&nbsp<br>Prior Notice Identifier:&nbsp<br>Required Response<br>&nbsp; Indicator Description:&nbsp<br>Response Date:&nbsp<br>Response Time:&nbsp<br>Subject:&nbsp<br></div><div id=headingData>006951446<br>Algonquin Gas Transmission, LLC<br>Critical notice<br>03/26/2026<br>09:00:00 AM<br>06/24/2026<br>08:45:45 AM<br>175690<br>Initiate<br>Operational Flow Order<br>03/26/2026<br>08:45:45 AM<br> <br><br>No response required<br> <br> <br>AGT Customer Specific Operational Flow Order<br></div></div><br><div id=bulletin><br><div id=heading>Notice Text:</div><br><p style=\\\"margin: 0in; line-height: 115%; font-size: 16px; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\\\"><a><span style=\\\"font-size: 16px; line-height: 115%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\\\">In order to maintain the operational integrity of the system, Algonquin Gas Transmission, LLC (AGT) is issuing an Operational Flow Order (OFO) pursuant to Section 26 of the General Terms and Conditions of AGT's FERC Gas Tariff,</span></a><span><span style=\\\"font-size: 16px; line-height: 115%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\\\"> effective 9:00 AM CCT March 26, 2026</span></span><span><span style=\\\"font-size: 16px; line-height: 115%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\\\">, for</span></span><span><span style=\\\"font-size: 16px; line-height: 115%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\\\"> certain delivery point parties on the AGT system. AGT has contacted the affected parties. </span></span></p> \\n<p style=\\\"margin: 0in; line-height: 115%; font-size: 16px; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\\\"><span><span style=\\\"font-size: 16px; line-height: 115%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\\\">&nbsp;</span></span></p> \\n<p style=\\\"margin: 0in; line-height: 115%; font-size: 16px; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\\\"><span><span style=\\\"font-size: 16px; line-height: 115%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\\\">This OFO does not affect the ability of AGT to receive or deliver quantities of gas for scheduled nominations to any customer or pipeline.</span></span></p> \\n<p style=\\\"margin: 0in; line-height: 115%; font-size: 16px; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\\\"><span><span style=\\\"font-size: 16px; line-height: 115%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\\\">&nbsp;</span></span></p> \\n<p style=\\\"margin: 0in; line-height: 115%; font-size: 16px; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\\\"><span><a><span style=\\\"font-size: 16px; line-height: 115%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\\\">During the effectiveness of this OFO, the notified parties must be balanced such that actual deliveries of gas out of the system must be equal to or greater than scheduled deliveries out of the system. The penalty shall apply to each dekatherm of actual delivery quantities that are less than scheduled quantities minus 250 Dth or 95% of scheduled delivery quantities.<span>&nbsp; </span></span></a></span></p> \\n<p style=\\\"margin: 0in; line-height: 115%; font-size: 16px; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\\\"><span><span><span style=\\\"font-size: 16px; line-height: 115%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\\\">&nbsp;</span></span></span></p> \\n<p style=\\\"margin: 0in; line-height: 115%; font-size: 16px; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\\\"><span><span style=\\\"font-size: 16px; line-height: 115%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\\\">The penalty will be equal to three times the arithmetic average of daily Platts Gas Daily \\\"Daily Price Survey\\\" posting for the High Common price for \\\"Algonquin, city-gates\\\" for the day on which such violation occurred as indicated in AGT's General Terms and Conditions Section 26.8. In addition, AGT will not permit retroactive nominations to avoid an OFO penalty except for primary firm no-notice nominations or shippers who can secure day ending Due Shipper supply for Due Pipe imbalances and Due Pipe supply for Due Shipper imbalances.</span></span></p> \\n<p style=\\\"margin: 0in; line-height: 115%; font-size: 16px; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\\\"><span><span style=\\\"font-size: 16px; line-height: 115%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\\\">&nbsp;</span></span></p> \\n<p style=\\\"margin: 0in; line-height: 115%; font-size: 16px; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\\\"><span><span style=\\\"font-size: 16px; line-height: 115%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\\\">The individual OFO(s) will remain in effect until further notice.</span></span></p> \\n<p style=\\\"margin: 0in; line-height: 115%; font-size: 16px; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\\\"><span><span style=\\\"font-size: 16px; line-height: 115%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\\\">&nbsp;</span></span></p> \\n<p style=\\\"margin: 0in; line-height: 115%; font-size: 16px; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\\\"><span><span style=\\\"font-size: 16px; line-height: 115%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\\\">Please contact your Operations Account Representative should you have any questions.</span></span></p> \\n<p style=\\\"margin: 0in; line-height: 115%; font-size: 16px; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size: 16px; line-height: 115%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\\\">&nbsp;</span></p> \\n<p style=\\\"margin: 0in; line-height: 115%; font-size: 16px; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size: 16px; line-height: 115%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\\\">Please refer to the table below for the effected AGT operational areas, dates, and tolerance percentages.</span></p> \\n<div> \\n <table border=\\\"1\\\" width=\\\"588\\\" style=\\\"width: 585px; border-collapse: collapse; border: none;\\\"> \\n  <tbody> \\n   <tr> \\n    <td width=\\\"126\\\" style=\\\"width: 125px; border: 1px solid windowtext; padding: 0in 7px;\\\"> <p style=\\\"margin: 0in; line-height: normal; font-size: 16px; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; text-align: center;\\\"><a><b><span style=\\\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\\\">Operational Area</span></b></a></p> </td> \\n    <td width=\\\"114\\\" style=\\\"width: 114px; border